To ensure the program's correct functionality, an array `stones` should be taken as input.The array `stones` must have a length of `n`.The array `stones` must consist of elements in the form of `[x<sub>i</sub> ,  y<sub>i</sub>]`, where each element represents the location of the `i<sup>th</sup>` stone.When the program is executed, it should perform calculations to determine the maximum number of stones that can be removed, and then return this value.To calculate the count of removable stones, the program should consider the stone locations.The largest possible number of stones that can be removed should be determined based on the given locations of the stones.